snippet.textDisplay: This song is such a blessing! It sums up my mum's prayer for her children, biological or not and family my entire life! She has always declared these words and having them in a song is a huge blessing! I've been declaring this over my family, and my future  family, and my future children over and over again! Amen!! I am currently living in China where it's honestly been a crazy couple of months, and this song has been a very timely encouragement! God has been and is still God over everything and His blessings are upon us each and everyday and I am so grateful! So take heart world, if He is for us, then who or what can be against us?

Exodus 20

 1  And Elohim spoke all these Words, saying,
 2  “I am יהוה your Elohim, who brought you out of the land of Mitsrayim, out of the house of slavery.
 3  “You have no other mighty ones against My face.
 4  “You do not make for yourself a carved image, or any likeness of that which is in the heavens above, or which is in the earth beneath, or which is in the waters under the earth,
 5  you do not bow down to them nor serve them. For I, יהוה your Elohim am a jealous Ěl, visiting the crookedness of the fathers on the children to the third and fourth generations of those who hate Me,
 6  but showing loving-commitment to thousands, to those who love Me and guard My commands.
 7  “You do not bring a the Name of יהוה your Elohim to naught, for יהוה does not leave the one unpunished who brings His Name to naught.
 8  “Remember the Sabbath day, to set it apart.
 9  “Six days you labour, and shall do all your work,
 10  but the seventh day is a Sabbath b of יהוה your Elohim. You do not do any work – you, nor your son, nor your daughter, nor your male servant, nor your female servant, nor your cattle, nor your stranger who is within your gates.
 11  “For in six days יהוה made the heavens and the earth, the sea, and all that is in them, and rested the seventh day. Therefore יהוה blessed the Sabbath day and set it apart.
 12  “Respect your father and your mother, so that your days are prolonged upon the soil which יהוה your Elohim is giving you.
 13  “You do not murder.
 14  “You do not commit adultery.
 15  “You do not steal.
 16  “You do not bear false witness against your neighbour.
 17  “You do not covet your neighbour’s house, you do not covet your neighbour’s wife, nor his male servant, nor his female servant, nor his ox, nor his donkey, or whatever belongs to your neighbour.”
 18  And all the people saw the thunders, the lightning flashes, the voice of the shophar, and the mountain smoking. And the people saw it, and they trembled and stood at a distance,
 19  and said to Mosheh, “You speak with us and we hear, but let not Elohim speak with us, lest we die.”
 20  And Mosheh said to the people, “Do not fear, for Elohim has come to prove you, and in order that His fear be before you,
❤so that you do not sin.”❤
 21  So the people stood at a distance, but Mosheh drew near the thick darkness where Elohim was.
 22  And יהוה said to Mosheh, “Say this to the children of Yisra’ĕl: ‘You yourselves have seen that I have spoken to you from the heavens...

HIS SPIRIT IS ALIVE!!
HALLELUYAH 🙌🏽💜👏🥰

Real confused how this is a worship song?
They're singing about God's blessing to his people, they're truly beautiful blessings but they aren't singing to God.
There is no honoring God, there is no literal worship of God. Just reclaiming his blessings over people. Which should be done in a church, and done over people, repeatedly and often, but it isn't singing to God.

snippet.textDisplay: God literally lead me to this song. Everything’s that’s going on right now about the corona virus and everything. Our world is in chaos. I was crying last night so afraid of what is going to happen and just wondering if everything will go back to normal. But then my mom turned on this song no knowing I was crying and afraid right next to her and it was like God heard me and he did and this song literally gave me peace, faith, hope, and strength. Even if this world is in chaos God told me I will be with you. This song rlly spoke to me last night. God is really using Kari and her husband to talk to his people and tell us everything is going to be alright. And everything will be alright. So everyone who’s afraid know God is for you and not against you. He’s given you favor along generations of your generations. He is with you he loves you. You are covered by his blood. God bless you everyone 💗 God is still with us 💗

I don't think this is a vertical worship song to God. Rather I think it's more a ministering song towards people horizontally. I'm not sure how I feel about that.

I must consider Colossians 3:16:
"Let the word of Christ dwell richly among you, in all wisdom teaching and admonishing one another [horizontal] through psalms, hymns, and spiritual songs, singing to God [vertical] with gratitude in your hearts."

snippet.textDisplay:
God gave me a beautiful vision about the corona virus pandemic as I was listening to this song . Everyone was in their homes in hiding leaving the streets in with no sound to be found. It was complete silence until I saw a few people boldly walking out of their homes onto the streets wearing the armor of god worshipping and speaking his word. It was activating the healing power of Jesus as it flooded the streets. Others could hear it in the distance as it sounded like a trumpet alarming them that it was ok to come out. They slowly started to walk out of their homes and as they did, they were greeted on their front door step by his presence. instantly they were healed.

He we shall not fear for everyone will rejoicing on the streets. Thank you Jesus that we will not be on locked down but locked and loaded and ready to profess to the world who you are. For your plan is better and your plan is ultimate truth.

I plead the blood of Jesus over our households and loved ones and ask that we boldly use these moments and our surroundings to glorify God. Who’s ready to worship the lord where most wouldn’t attempt and watch him move like never before??

snippet.textDisplay:
It appears the scriptures they used consist of parts of Psalm 67, Psalm 128, Psalm 139 and Numbers 6:22-27. I encourage you to read them in full! Dig in His Word! You don't have to wait for someone to write a song with scripture in it to be blessed by His Word. Consider Hebrews 4:12-16 "For the word of God is living and active, sharper than any two-edged sword, piercing to the division of soul and of spirit, of joints and of marrow, and discerning the thoughts and intentions of the heart. 13And no creature is hidden from his sight, but all are naked and exposed to the eyes of him to whom we must give account.
14Since then we have a great high priest who has passed through the heavens, Jesus, the Son of God, let us hold fast our confession. 15For we do not have a high priest who is unable to sympathize with our weaknesses, but one who in every respect has been tempted as we are, yet without sin. 16Let us then with confidence draw near to the throne of grace, that we may receive mercy and find grace to help in time of need." The two chapters before this, read Hebrews 3 and 4, are taking about the same people the blessing in the song, from Numbers, was written to...obedience it God is key! God bless!

snippet.textDisplay:
As I've listened over this song and read through the Numbers 33:24-26 passage that the blessing primarily comes from, I am reminded that God's blessings are always poured out to those who are obedient to Him.

This song isn't really about receiving but is a call to obedience. Exodus 20 is the chapter containing the Ten Commandments. The first command is to have no other god before God and to make no idol. Exodus 20:5-6, "for I, the Lord your God, am a jealous God, punishing the children for the sin of the parents to the third and fourth generation of those who hate me, 6 but showing love to a thousand generations of those who love me and keep my commandments."


If you want to receive the blessings of the Lord, love Him and keep His commandments, whether you agree or like those commandments. Do not fall in love with a beautiful song or a beautiful idea of God, but fall in love with God Himself and out of that love, submit your health, family, preferences, sexuality, ideologies, addictions, finances (infinite list) to Him. THEN, "may His favor be upon you to a thousand generations and your family and your children and their children and their children. Amen."
